Adding eina's macport to your existing macports system
======================================================

1. Install eina's port files
   $ [ -d  /opt/local/var/macports/sources/eina.sourceforge.net/release/ports/ ] || sudo mkdir -p  /opt/local/var/macports/sources/eina.sourceforge.net/release/ports/
   $ sudo rsync -a --delete-after --exclude=.svn eina-x.x.x/macports /opt/local/var/macports/sources/eina.sourceforge.net/release/ports/

2. Configure macports to use eina's ports. Add this line on top of your /opt/local/etc/macports/sources.conf file
   file:///opt/local/var/macports/sources/eina.sourceforge.net/release/ports/

3. Install eina:
   sudo port install gstreamer gst-plugins-base +no_x11 gst-plugins-good gst-plugins-ugly gtk2 +no_x11 +quartz eina sqlite3

   (gst-plugins-base for ogg vorbis decoder)
   (gst-plugins-ugly for mad decoder)
   (gst-plugins-good for OSX audio sink)
   (sqlite3 for some plugins)

4. Run eina
   Open a terminal (use spotlight) and type: eina
